==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bournonite
<hw>Bour"non*ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
Count <etsep>Bournon</etsep>, a mineralogist.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of a steel-gray to black color and metallic luster,
occurring crystallized, often in twin crystals shaped like cogwheels
(wheel ore), also massive. It is a sulphide of antimony, lead, and
copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bournous</ent>⟦br⟧
